<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB09211</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROHIBITING THE IMPORTATION OF SOLID WASTE MATERIALS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Provides for the definition of solid waste as defined in R.A. No.9003 and its IRR as follows:

"Solid waste shall refer to all discarded household, commercial waste, non-hazardous institutional and industrial waste, street sweepings, construction debris, agricultural waste, and other non-hazardous/non-toxic solid waste."

Penalizes any entity or person, foreigner, business entity owner/president/manager/sr. officers, or government official/employees who shall import any solid waste for use, treatment, or processing in violation of this Act with corresponding punishment and liabilities.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CASTELO, WINSTON &quot;WINNIE&quot;</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-06-04</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ECOLOGY ON 2019-06-04</td></tr></table>